-- Microsoft Tops U.S. Retail Game Console Sales With Xbox
-- B y   C l i f f   E d w a r d s
-- 2013-05-16T22:38:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-16/microsoft-tops-u-s-retail-game-console-sales-with-xbox.html
Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  said U.S. retailers
sold 130,000 Xbox 360 game consoles in April, helping it retain
the top-selling spot for the 28th straight month.  April spending on all Xbox products, including the console,
Kinect motion-sensing peripheral and software, totaled $208
million, Redmond, Washington-based Microsoft said today in an e-mail, citing NPD Group Inc. data. Microsoft sold 236,000
consoles a year ago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cliff Edwards in San Francisco at 
